{
  "texts": [
    "Challenges in Model DeploymentDeploying RL models in educational environments often requires significant technical and infrastructural upgrades.",
    "Many schools and institutions lack the resources or expertise to integrate advanced AI systems effectively.",
    "Furthermore, RL's reliance on trial-and-error learning can lead to unpredictable behaviors during deployment, creating potential disruptions in resource management or student interactions [17].",
    "For example, early-stage models might allocate resources inefficiently before achieving optimal performance.To mitigate these risks, models should be deployed in phases, starting with small-scale pilot projects.",
    "These pilots allow for controlled testing and refinement, ensuring that systems are stable and effective before scaling them to broader applications."
  ]
}